SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Warm up first — get your heart rate elevated before the working sets.
2. Pick a starting pace you can sustain conversationally.
3. Maintain steady form throughout — no cheating with momentum.
4. Breathe in a sustainable rhythm; do not hold your breath.
5. Cool down for at least 3 minutes at low intensity.
6. Breathing: Nose-in, mouth-out when pace allows — it regulates effort. Match breathing to rhythm: 2 in / 2 out is a good starting cadence. If you can talk in short sentences, you are at a sustainable zone-2 effort.
7. Form check: Maintain steady form throughout — quality beats raw speed.
8. Form check: Avoid choppy posture changes; let the work breathe.
9. The Assault Airbike Sprint Speed mainly trains your Quadriceps (Quadriceps Femoris), Hamstrings (Biceps Femoris, Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus), Glutes (gluteus maximus, gluteus mideus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'cardio_bike',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=cardio_bike] ACSM GETP 11th ed. ch.6-7 — aerobic exercise prescription$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
