INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set up over the bar with feet hip-width, bar over mid-foot.
2. Take a clean grip (just outside the legs), tight back, chest up.
3. Drive through the floor, then aggressively shrug and pull the bar high.
4. Pull yourself under and rotate the elbows around to a front-rack.
5. Catch in a front squat, stand up, and reset.
6. Breathing: Inhale and brace at the start of the lift. Hold the brace through the pull — let the breath out at lockout. Reset the breath fully between every single rep — these are max-effort attempts.
7. Form check: Keep the bar PATH straight up — no arching out and back.
8. Form check: Lock the lats and keep the bar close to the body throughout the pull.
9. The Barbell Clean And Jerk mainly trains your Quadriceps (Quadriceps Femoris), Glutes (gluteus maximus, gluteus mideus), Shoulders (Deltoids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'olympic_clean',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=olympic_clean] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.15 — Olympic-lift technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = 'a569ad67-787a-48de-b5bf-7a8a37dd587a'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = 'a569ad67-787a-48de-b5bf-7a8a37dd587a');
