SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set up in a long lunge stance, rear foot elevated on a bench.
2. Square the hips, brace the core, eyes forward.
3. Lower the back knee straight down toward the floor.
4. Front shin should stay roughly vertical at the bottom.
5. Drive through the front heel back to the start.
6. Breathing: Take a big belly-breath before you descend and brace your core. Hold the brace through the bottom of the rep. Exhale forcefully on the drive up.
7. Form check: Weight in your heels and mid-foot.
8. Form check: Go as deep as your mobility allows with good form.
9. The Bulgarian Split Squat mainly trains your Quadriceps (Quadriceps Femoris), Glutes (gluteus maximus, gluteus mideus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'split_squat',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=split_squat] NSCA Essentials of Strength Training & Conditioning 4th ed. (Haff & Triplett 2016) ch.13 — squat technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
