INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Lie on your back, knees bent, feet flat near your glutes.
2. Tuck the pelvis and brace the core.
3. Drive through the heels to lift the hips.
4. Squeeze the glutes hard at the top — ribs stacked over hips.
5. Lower under control to just above the floor.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bottom — pelvis tucked, ribs down. Exhale as you drive the hips up and squeeze the glutes. Inhale at the top before lowering with control.
7. Form check: Tuck the chin and the pelvis — ribs down, not flared.
8. Form check: Drive through the heels, not the toes.
9. The Dumbbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge mainly trains your Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'glute_bridge',
