SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Hinge at the hips with a slight knee bend.
2. Keep your back flat and core engaged.
3. Grip the weight with arms extended.
4. Pull the weight toward your lower chest/upper abs.
5. Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the stretched position with arms extended. Exhale as you pull the weight in and squeeze the back. Inhale again on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Initiate the pull with the back, not the arms.
8. Form check: Core tight — do not let the lower back arch.
9. The Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row mainly trains your Back (Latissimus Dorsi, Rhomboids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'barbell_row',
