SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set the seat / sled depth so your knees can hit ~90° without pinching.
2. Place feet shoulder-width on the platform, slightly toed out.
3. Press the safety latches off, control the negative.
4. Lower until thighs are parallel — do NOT let your lower back round off the pad.
5. Drive through the whole foot, locking out without slamming the knees.
6. Breathing: Inhale on the descent — fill the belly and brace. Exhale on the press — never let the lower back round off the pad. Reset the breath between reps.
7. Form check: Lower until thighs are parallel — do NOT round the lower back off the pad.
8. Form check: Knees track over the toes; do NOT let them collapse inward.
9. The Horizontal Leg Press mainly trains your Quadriceps (Quadriceps Femoris), Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'leg_press',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=leg_press] NSCA Essentials of Strength Training & Conditioning 4th ed. (Haff & Triplett 2016) ch.13 — squat technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
