INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library_manual', instructions, $instr$1. Pick a rope — handles should reach armpit height when you stand on the middle.
2. Elbows close to the ribs, wrists do the work — not the shoulders.
3. Stay on the balls of your feet, jumping just 1–2 inches off the floor.
4. Keep a soft knee bend; land quietly to spare your joints.
5. Build rhythm before you chase speed.
6. Breathing: Inhale through the eccentric / loading phase. Exhale forcefully on the explosive concentric (the jump or push). Reset the breath between reps — do not hold under repeated impact.
7. Form check: Keep the elbows close to the ribs — let the wrists do the work.
8. Form check: Stay on the balls of the feet, jumping just 1–2 inches.
9. The Jump Rope Alternate Foot Step mainly trains your calves. If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'jump_rope',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=jump_rope] ACSM GETP 11th ed. ch.6-7 — aerobic exercise prescription$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
