SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Sit on a bench, lean forward, brace the working elbow on the inside of your thigh.
2. Let the dumbbell hang with palm up.
3. Curl up while the upper arm stays glued to the leg.
4. Squeeze hard at the top.
5. Lower with full control to a long arm.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bottom with arms fully extended. Exhale as you curl the weight up. Inhale on the slow eccentric back down.
7. Form check: Upper arms stay stationary — do not let elbows drift forward.
8. Form check: No swinging the weight or rocking the torso.
9. The Kettlebell Concentration Curl mainly trains your Biceps (Biceps Brachii, Short Head). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'concentration_curl',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=concentration_curl] NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.13 — single-joint resistance technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = 'c847f1ce-7591-4bc3-b19f-8756b94d5ad0'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = 'c847f1ce-7591-4bc3-b19f-8756b94d5ad0');
UPDATE public.exercise_library SET instructions = $instr$1. Sit on a bench, lean forward, brace the working elbow on the inside of your thigh.
2. Let the dumbbell hang with palm up.
3. Curl up while the upper arm stays glued to the leg.
4. Squeeze hard at the top.
5. Lower with full control to a long arm.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bottom with arms fully extended. Exhale as you curl the weight up. Inhale on the slow eccentric back down.
7. Form check: Upper arms stay stationary — do not let elbows drift forward.
8. Form check: No swinging the weight or rocking the torso.
9. The Kettlebell Concentration Curl mainly trains your Biceps (Biceps Brachii, Short Head). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$ WHERE id = 'c847f1ce-7591-4bc3-b19f-8756b94d5ad0';

