SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Settle into the preacher bench — armpits sit at the top of the pad.
2. Grip the bar with palms up, slightly narrower than shoulders.
3. Curl the bar up under tension — do NOT bounce off the pad.
4. Squeeze the biceps at the top.
5. Lower fully but stop just before complete elbow lockout.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bottom with arms fully extended. Exhale as you curl the weight up. Inhale on the slow eccentric back down.
7. Form check: Upper arms stay stationary — do not let elbows drift forward.
8. Form check: No swinging the weight or rocking the torso.
