INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand with feet hip-to-shoulder width, bar in the front rack on your shoulders.
2. Brace your core and squeeze your glutes — ribs stacked over hips.
3. Press the bar overhead in a vertical line, moving your head through.
4. Lock out with biceps near the ears and the bar over mid-foot.
5. Lower with control back to the front rack, reset, repeat.
6. Breathing: Inhale and brace the core BEFORE the press starts. Hold the brace through the push. Exhale at lockout, reset the breath, then lower.
7. Form check: Squeeze the glutes — they protect the lower back.
8. Form check: Press the bar in a vertical line — head moves through at lockout.
9. The Landmine Overhead Press mainly trains your Shoulders (Anterior Deltoids, Lateral Deltoids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'overhead_press',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=overhead_press] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.13; NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.13 — overhead pressing, neutral rib position$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = 'dadb408a-150d-4888-ac95-20e161e2e04c'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = 'dadb408a-150d-4888-ac95-20e161e2e04c');
