9. The Landmine Overhead Press mainly trains your Shoulders (Anterior Deltoids, Lateral Deltoids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$ WHERE id = 'dadb408a-150d-4888-ac95-20e161e2e04c';

INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand tall, bar at hip height, feet hip-width.
2. Maintain a slight, fixed knee bend — do not turn this into a squat.
3. Hinge at the hips, pushing them BACK as the bar slides down the thighs.
4. Stop just below the knee or where your hamstring stretch peaks.
5. Drive hips forward to stand — finish with glutes squeezed, not lower-back arched.
6. Breathing: Take a big breath into your belly at the top before setting up. Hold the brace throughout the pull — do not exhale mid-rep. Exhale at lockout, reset the breath before the next rep.
7. Form check: Hips back, NOT a squat — knee bend stays fixed.
8. Form check: Bar slides down the thighs; never drift away from the body.
9. The Landmine Romanian Deadlift mainly trains your Back (Erector Spinae), Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'rdl',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=rdl] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.13; McGill, Low Back Disorders 2nd ed. — neutral-spine hip hinge$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = 'ef5aa777-b4e1-4140-a0dc-ced7bbc09b7c'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = 'ef5aa777-b4e1-4140-a0dc-ced7bbc09b7c');
UPDATE public.exercise_library SET instructions = $instr$1. Stand tall, bar at hip height, feet hip-width.
2. Maintain a slight, fixed knee bend — do not turn this into a squat.
3. Hinge at the hips, pushing them BACK as the bar slides down the thighs.
4. Stop just below the knee or where your hamstring stretch peaks.
5. Drive hips forward to stand — finish with glutes squeezed, not lower-back arched.
6. Breathing: Take a big breath into your belly at the top before setting up. Hold the brace throughout the pull — do not exhale mid-rep. Exhale at lockout, reset the breath before the next rep.
7. Form check: Hips back, NOT a squat — knee bend stays fixed.
8. Form check: Bar slides down the thighs; never drift away from the body.
9. The Landmine Romanian Deadlift mainly trains your Back (Erector Spinae), Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$ WHERE id = 'ef5aa777-b4e1-4140-a0dc-ced7bbc09b7c';

INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Sit with knees bent, lean back to ~45°.
2. Hold a weight (or hands together) at chest level.
3. Lift the feet (advanced) or keep them planted (beginner).
4. Rotate from the trunk — twist the weight side to side.
5. Pause briefly each side; do not let the lower back round.
6. Breathing: Inhale on the eccentric / lengthening phase. Exhale forcefully as you contract the abs at the top. Empty the lungs at the peak contraction for maximum recruitment.
7. Form check: Rotate from the trunk, NOT the arms.
8. Form check: Keep the lower back flat — do not let it round.
9. The Landmine Russian Twist mainly trains your Obliques (External and Internal Obliques). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'russian_twist',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=russian_twist] NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.9; McGill, Low Back Disorders 2nd ed. — trunk / core training$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
