INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand between the cable stacks (or set up in the pec-deck/bench).
2. Soft bend in the elbows — never lock them out.
3. Step one foot forward (cable) for a stable base, chest up.
4. Bring the handles together in front of your chest in a sweeping arc.
5. Squeeze your chest at the midpoint, then reverse with control.
6. Breathing: Inhale on the way out as your chest stretches. Exhale as you bring the handles together and squeeze. Keep the breath smooth — never hold it for multiple reps.
7. Form check: Soft bend in the elbows the whole time — never lock them.
8. Form check: Hug a tree — chest leads, not the arms.
9. The Pec Deck Fly Machine Flies mainly trains your Chest (Pectoralis Major). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'fly',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=fly] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.13; NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.13 — horizontal pressing$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
