SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand with feet hip-width apart, bar over mid-foot.
2. Grip the bar just outside your legs.
3. Keep your back flat and chest up.
4. Take the slack out of the bar before pulling.
5. Drive through your heels and push hips forward.
6. Breathing: Take a big breath into your belly at the top before setting up. Hold the brace throughout the pull — do not exhale mid-rep. Exhale at lockout, reset the breath before the next rep.
7. Form check: Never round the lower back.
8. Form check: Keep the bar close to the body throughout.
9. The Plate Deadlift mainly trains your Hamstrings (Biceps Femoris, Semitendinosus), Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'deadlift',
