SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Anchor your upper arm — pin elbow to your side or brace on a bench.
2. Start with your forearm bent at ~90°.
3. Extend the weight back until your arm is straight.
4. Squeeze the triceps at full extension.
5. Return slowly — control the negative.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bent-elbow starting position. Exhale as you extend the weight back / overhead. Inhale on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Pin the elbow — the upper arm does NOT move.
8. Form check: Full extension at the top, but do not lock out hard.
9. The Plate Overhead Tricep Extension mainly trains your Triceps (Triceps Brachii, Long Head). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'triceps_extension',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=triceps_extension] NASM EPFT 6th ed. ch.13 — single-joint resistance technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
