SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand tall with feet hip-width apart, weights at the sides if used.
2. Step forward into a long lunge — front knee tracks over the toes.
3. Drive off the back foot and step THROUGH into the next lunge.
4. Maintain an upright torso the whole way.
5. Cover the prescribed distance, then turn around or reset.
6. Breathing: Inhale as you step out and descend. Exhale as you drive through the front heel and stand.
7. Form check: Front knee tracks over the toes — never caves inward.
8. Form check: Step long enough that the rear knee can comfortably reach the floor.
9. The Plate Overhead Walking Lunge mainly trains your Quadriceps (Quadriceps Femoris), Glutes (Gluteus Maximus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'walking_lunge',
