SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, palms facing DOWN.
2. Take a slightly narrower than shoulder-width grip.
3. Keep elbows pinned at the sides.
4. Curl the weight up using your forearms and biceps brachialis.
5. Lower with control — forearms will fatigue fast.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the bottom with arms fully extended. Exhale as you curl the weight up. Inhale on the slow eccentric back down.
7. Form check: Upper arms stay stationary — do not let elbows drift forward.
8. Form check: No swinging the weight or rocking the torso.
9. The Reverse Curl Barbell mainly trains your Forearms (Brachioradialis). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'reverse_curl',
