   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Sit tall with feet braced, knees soft, chest up.
2. Grip the handle with arms extended, shoulders pulled down.
3. Pull the handle to your sternum — drive the elbows back.
4. Squeeze the shoulder blades together at the end range.
5. Return slowly to a full stretch with the lats engaged.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the stretched position with arms extended. Exhale as you pull the weight in and squeeze the back. Inhale again on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Initiate the pull with the back, not the arms.
8. Form check: Core tight — do not let the lower back arch.
9. The Seated Cable Row V Bar Machine mainly trains your Middle Back (Latissimus Dorsi, Teres Major). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'cable_row',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=cable_row] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.13 — rowing / pulling technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
