SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Move into the position slowly — stop at the first point of mild tension.
2. Hold without bouncing; static stretches respond to time, not force.
3. Breathe into the stretch — inhale deeply, exhale and ease a touch deeper.
4. Aim for 30–60 seconds per side; never push into sharp pain.
5. Come out as deliberately as you went in.
6. Breathing: Inhale deeply through the nose into the belly. Exhale slowly through the mouth and ease a fraction deeper into the stretch. Never hold your breath — breathing is what allows tissue to release.
7. Form check: Move slowly into the position; never bounce.
8. Form check: Breathe deeply — exhalations let the tissue lengthen.
9. The Seated Single-Leg Toe Touch Hamstring Stretch mainly trains your Hamstrings (Biceps Femoris, Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'stretch',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=stretch] ACSM's Guidelines for Exercise Testing & Prescription 11th ed. (2021) ch.6 — flexibility training$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = 'ac7348a4-0b5d-4070-bb90-1f35af666367'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = 'ac7348a4-0b5d-4070-bb90-1f35af666367');
UPDATE public.exercise_library SET instructions = $instr$1. Move into the position slowly — stop at the first point of mild tension.
2. Hold without bouncing; static stretches respond to time, not force.
3. Breathe into the stretch — inhale deeply, exhale and ease a touch deeper.
4. Aim for 30–60 seconds per side; never push into sharp pain.
5. Come out as deliberately as you went in.
6. Breathing: Inhale deeply through the nose into the belly. Exhale slowly through the mouth and ease a fraction deeper into the stretch. Never hold your breath — breathing is what allows tissue to release.
7. Form check: Move slowly into the position; never bounce.
8. Form check: Breathe deeply — exhalations let the tissue lengthen.
9. The Seated Single-Leg Toe Touch Hamstring Stretch mainly trains your Hamstrings (Biceps Femoris, Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$ WHERE id = 'ac7348a4-0b5d-4070-bb90-1f35af666367';

