INSERT INTO public.exercise_instruction_backup
  (id, source_table, old_instructions, new_instructions, movement_class,
   source_citation, rewrite_batch)
SELECT id, 'exercise_library', instructions, $instr$1. Set the bar / TRX handles roughly waist height.
2. Hang underneath with arms straight, body in a straight line.
3. Brace the core and squeeze the glutes — no hip sag.
4. Pull your chest to the bar/handles, elbows trace the ribs.
5. Lower with control to a full hang and repeat.
6. Breathing: Inhale at the stretched position with arms extended. Exhale as you pull the weight in and squeeze the back. Inhale again on the controlled return.
7. Form check: Glutes and core braced — no hip sag at any point.
8. Form check: Pull until the bar/handles touch your chest.
9. The Suspension Trainer With Grips Inverted Row mainly trains your Back (Latissimus Dorsi), Shoulders (Posterior Deltoids). If you are newer to it, start light and add load only once the movement feels controlled, and on heavier sets end the set when your form or brace breaks down rather than grinding out a risky rep.$instr$, 'inverted_row',
  $instr$[rule | engine=exercise_instruction_copy.dart | class=inverted_row] NSCA ESSC 4th ed. ch.13 — rowing / pulling technique$instr$, '2084-2026-05-18'
FROM public.exercise_library WHERE id = '1a23c0bc-c661-4402-ace1-0f91ace8c4b8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.exercise_instruction_backup
                  WHERE id = '1a23c0bc-c661-4402-ace1-0f91ace8c4b8');
